  "prompt": "What is the best way to clean a spray bottle before reusing it?",
  "response": "Here are some effective methods to clean a spray bottle before reusing it:\n\n1. Basic cleaning method:\n- Empty the bottle completely\n- Rinse with warm water\n- Fill with a mixture of warm water and mild dish soap\n- Spray and rinse thoroughly\n- Let it air dry completely\n\n2. Disinfecting method:\n- Rinse with warm water\n- Fill with a solution of 1 part white vinegar to 3 parts water\n- Let sit for 5-10 minutes\n- Rinse thoroughly with clean water\n- Air dry\n\n3. For stubborn residue or strong chemicals:\n- Use rubbing alcohol to rinse and sanitize\n- Alternatively, use a weak bleach solution (1 tablespoon bleach per cup of water)\n- Rinse multiple times with clean water\n- Allow to air dry completely\n\n4. Additional tips:\n- Take the spray nozzle apart and clean it separately\n- Use a bottle brush for hard-to-reach areas\n- Ensure the bottle is completely dry before refilling\n- Check for any remaining odors or stains before reuse\n\nAlways choose a cleaning method appropriate to the previous contents of the bottle.",
